solution: Following the order of operations, we do the division and the multiplication before the addition and subtraction: \[6\div 6 - 6 + 6\times 6 = 1 -6+36 = -5+36 =\boxed{31}.\]
model_solution:
Step 1:  We need to follow the order of operations (PEMDAS/BODMAS) to solve the expression $6\div6-6+6\times6$. 
$
\begin{array}{l}6\div6-6+6\times6 \\ 1-6+36\end{array}
$
Step 2:  We need to evaluate $1-6+36$.
$
\begin{array}{l} 1-6+36 \\ -5+36\end{array}
$
$
\begin{array}{l}  -5+36 \\ 31\end{array}
$
Step 3: 
$
\begin{array}{l}31\end{array}
$
